Context
Agents are generic on their
context
type. Context is a dependency-injection tool: it's an object you create and pass to
Runner.run()
, that is passed to every agent, tool, handoff etc, and it serves as a grab bag of dependencies and state for the agent run. You can provide any Python object as the context.
Read the
context guide
for the full
RunContextWrapper
surface, shared usage tracking, nested
tool_input
, and serialization caveats.
