Short-term memory
When an
entrypoint
is defined with a
checkpointer
, it stores information between successive invocations on the same
thread id
in
checkpoints
.
This allows accessing the state from the previous invocation using the
previous
parameter.
By default, the
previous
parameter is the return value of the previous invocation.
