=
{
"PATH"
:
"/usr/bin:/bin"
}),
)
How it works:
Extends
FilesystemBackend
with the
execute
tool for running shell commands on the host.
Commands run directly on your machine using
subprocess.run(shell=True)
with no sandboxing.
Supports
timeout
(default 120s),
max_output_bytes
(default 100,000),
env
, and
inherit_env
for environment variables.
Shell commands use
root_dir
as the working directory but can access any path on the system.
Best for:
Local coding assistants and development tools
Quick iteration during development when you trust the agent
